🧠 Final Clean Flow (What You Should Say)
User opens React app → UI calls backend to check session.
If no session, backend redirects to PingFederate login.

After successful login, PingFederate redirects back to backend with an authorization code.
Backend exchanges this code with PingFederate to get access and refresh tokens.

Backend stores these tokens securely on the server and creates a session, sending a session cookie to the browser.

UI then makes API calls with the session cookie, and backend uses the stored token to validate and process requests, verifying it using PingFederate’s public key.
